"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-04-12-heart-broken-olympic-triple-jump-champion-rojas-paris-games\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"CARACAS,\\u00a0Venezuela\\u00a0(AFP)- Reigning Olympic women's triple jump champion Yulimar Rojas said on Friday she had injured her Achilles tendon and will miss the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 7, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caracas\", \"score\": 0.9999999995945927, \"rank\": 4.0540713127203425e-10, \"text\": \"CARACAS\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caracas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caracas\"}, {\"begin\": 9, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\", \"score\": 0.9999999589158515, \"rank\": 2.3457503639768986e-08, \"text\": \"Venezuela\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\"}, {\"begin\": 72, \"end\": 85, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yulimar_Rojas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yulimar Rojas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yulimar_Rojas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yulimar_Rojas\"}, {\"begin\": 121, \"end\": 129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"score\": 0.9999992403743975, \"rank\": 7.596260697953753e-07, \"text\": \"Achilles\", \"types\": [\"Q4936952\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 28-year-old Venezuelan said she had torn her Achilles during a training jump in Spain and had undergone surgery in Madrid on Thursday.\", \"from\": 169, \"to\": 307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 185, \"end\": 195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\", \"score\": 0.9994371019811964, \"rank\": 0.0005632142747684364, \"text\": \"Venezuelan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\"}, {\"begin\": 218, \"end\": 226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"score\": 0.9999992403743975, \"rank\": 7.596260697953753e-07, \"text\": \"Achilles\", \"types\": [\"Q4936952\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\"}, {\"begin\": 253, \"end\": 258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.845046239461421, \"rank\": 0.1810726494867252, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}, {\"begin\": 288, \"end\": 294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madrid\", \"score\": 0.9998168308807812, \"rank\": 0.00018284154024298847, \"text\": \"Madrid\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madrid\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madrid\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My heart is broken and I want to say sorry that I will not be able to take part in Paris 2024,\\\"\\u00a0said Rojas in a statement on her social media accounts.\", \"from\": 309, \"to\": 461, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 393, \"end\": 403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999993179, \"rank\": 7.566756329781562e-13, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the statement, accompanied by a picture of her in a hospital bed, Rojas said that as she landed from the training jump, \\\"I felt an intense pain, which has been diagnosed as an injury to the left Achilles tendon\\\".\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 678, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 661, \"end\": 669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"score\": 0.9999992403743975, \"rank\": 7.596260697953753e-07, \"text\": \"Achilles\", \"types\": [\"Q4936952\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rojas won the silver medal at the 2016 Rio Olympics and then took the Olympic title at the Covid-delayed Tokyo Games in 2021.\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 805, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She dramatically won the fourth of her outdoor world titles in Budapest last year with her last-round leap, moving from eighth place to gold medal position with a winning jump of 15.08m.\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 993, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 870, \"end\": 878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"score\": 0.9999999784793092, \"rank\": 2.1494908469153668e-08, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rojas is also the world record holder in the event with a jump of 15.74m in 2022.\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1076, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was voted the World Athlete of the Year for women's field events last year and would have been a hot favourite to retain her Olympic title in Paris.\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1224, \"end\": 1229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999791066332, \"rank\": 2.089326580515014e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Today I feel very emotionally affected about not being able to defend my Olympic title\\u2026 but I must stop, take that in, recover and return with a lot of strength to continue to fly together,\\\" Rojas said in a message to her fans.\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1460, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics take place from July 26 to August 11.\", \"from\": 1462, \"to\": 1518, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Venezuela, Rojas is a national heroine.\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1523, \"end\": 1532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\", \"score\": 0.9999999589158515, \"rank\": 2.3457503639768986e-08, \"text\": \"Venezuela\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her face appears on huge frescoes, photos adorn many walls and commercials featuring the star athlete on television are a common feature.\", \"from\": 1564, \"to\": 1701, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She is the only woman and the only track and field athlete to win Olympic gold for Venezuela, which has three male champions in other sports.\", \"from\": 1703, \"to\": 1844, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1786, \"end\": 1795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\", \"score\": 0.9999999589158515, \"rank\": 2.3457503639768986e-08, \"text\": \"Venezuela\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venezuela\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among them, Ruben Limardo, a fencing gold medallist in London in 2012, said Rojas remains an inspiration to the country ahead of the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1858, \"end\": 1871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rub\\u00e9n_Limardo\", \"score\": 0.999999760887505, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ruben Limardo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rub\\u00e9n_Limardo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rub\\u00e9n_Limardo\"}, {\"begin\": 1901, \"end\": 1907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999998745188429, \"rank\": 6.807902301258433e-08, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Yuli, every step we take, we will do so in thinking that you are with us in body, soul and heart.\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2094, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Warrior, you can rise and fly again,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2095, \"to\": 2141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Venezuelan President Nicolas Maduro added: \\\"All my love, my solidarity, my support.\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2143, \"end\": 2163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_Venezuela\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Venezuelan President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_Venezuela\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_Venezuela\"}, {\"begin\": 2164, \"end\": 2178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00e1s_Maduro\", \"score\": 0.9999999836136341, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicolas Maduro\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00e1s_Maduro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00e1s_Maduro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We love you and we know your commitment and your discipline.\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are a warrior of life, an example for young people.\\\"\", \"from\": 2288, \"to\": 2344, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Based in Spain, Rojas emerged from the deprived neighbourhoods of Puerto La Cruz, around 300km from capital city, Caracas.\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2355, \"end\": 2360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.845046239461421, \"rank\": 0.1810726494867252, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}, {\"begin\": 2412, \"end\": 2426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_la_Cruz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Puerto La Cruz\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_la_Cruz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_la_Cruz\"}, {\"begin\": 2460, \"end\": 2467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caracas\", \"score\": 0.9999999995945927, \"rank\": 4.0540713127203425e-10, \"text\": \"Caracas\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caracas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caracas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We raised Yuli in this humble universe with a lot of problems.\", \"from\": 2470, \"to\": 2533, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She rose, rose, rose\\u2026\\\", proudly remembered her mother Yuleisi Rodriguez, interviewed by AFP before the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2622, \"end\": 2625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9999999999974989, \"rank\": 1.6708434219801002e-12, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"HOUSE RULES  Comments are closed.\", \"from\": 2651, \"to\": 2684, \"entities\": []}]}"